Location_Name: Augusta Creek at mouth, above Poverty Gulch
Arsenic sampling site 1 on North Fork of Coal Creek
Location_Description: Coal Creek 8 meters upstream of confluence with unnamed tributary that enters from the south.  The mainstem of Coal Creek is surrounded by a willow complex. This site was established for the Preliminary As Study NPS project in 2012.

Location_Name: Arsenic sampling site 2 on South Fork of Coal Creek
Location_Description: South fork of Coal Creek; 5 meters upstream of confluence with north fork of Coal Creek.  Cobble bottom for 5 meters then upstream sections are organic bottom

Location_Name: Lower Ender Mill arsenic sampling site 3
Location_Description: Lower Ender Mill.  ~60 m North (downstream) of potential contamination source along edge of willow complex. Incised channel into organic soil, meandering and braided.

Location_Name: Upper Ender Mill arsenic sampling site 3
Location_Description: Upper Ender Mill.  Upstream of potential contamination source, approximately 50 m SE of bare earth area.  Incised channel through willow complex.

Location_Name: Arsenic sampling site OPP
Location_Description: Culvert connecting the triangle of land between Kebler Pass Road and the road to Irwin.  Taken downstream of road.  Upstream of road=impounded wetland, downstream of road=small cobble channel

Location_Name: Baxter Creek at mouth, above Poverty Gulch
Bog drainage upstream of Kebler Pass Road and Coal Creek

The Wagon Road Trail begins about 180 feet west of the BOG-00 site and their is a small parking spot right next to the site.

Location_Name: First unnamed tributary downstream of BOG-00 above Kebler Pass Rd; sample collected about 5 m above rd. The site is approximately 100 m downstream of BOG-00 and 55 m upstream of CULVERT #1. The water drains from a breached area on the fen ditch.

Second unnamed tributary/seep downstream of BOG-00 above Kebler Pass Road; sample collected about 5 m above rd.  The site is approximately 135 m downstream of BOG-00 and about 20 m above CULVERT #2. The water drains from a breached area on the fen ditch.

Third unnamed tributary downstream of BOG-00 above Kebler Pass Rd;  collected about 5 m above rd.  Flows from BOG-OPP-1, BOG-OPP-2, & BOG-OPP-3 combine in the ditch immediately above CULVERT #3. The water drains from a breached area on the fen ditch.

Location_Name: North fork of Coal Creek near Kebler Pass "Y"

Location_Name: North fork of Coal Creek just upstream of Kebler Pass "Y"

Location_Name: Coal Creek below Irwin town site and the Forest Queen Mine
The largest/main tributary of Coal Creek, approximately 75 yards downstream of the last man-made Forest Queen Mine pond and below the Irwin Townsite.

First culvert downstream of BOG-00 and immediately below BOG-OPP-3. The culvert recieves flow from BOG-OPP-1, BOG-OPP-2, and BOG-OPP-3.  The culvert goes under Kebler Pass rd at BOG-OPP-3. The culvert is black corrugated plastic.

CULVERT #2 is about 190 m down from CULVERT #1. There are not typically surface tributaries between CULVERT #1 and CULVERT #2.  Groundwater seeps from the road cut-slope and water that by-passed CULVERT #1 create the flow at CULVERT #2.

Third culvert below BOG-00. There are not typically tributaries between CULVERT #2 & CULVERT #3. Groundwater seeps & dispersed surface flow create flow in the ditch immediatley downstream of CULVERT #2.

The fifth culvert downstream of BOG-00. There are two tributaries between CULVERT #4 and CULVERT #5. The second tributary accounts for about 80 percent of the flow at CULVERT #5. The second tributary likely drains a portion of the Gossan.
